If you're looking for a serene and beautiful place to pray, reflect, and connect with your faith, I highly recommend this mosque. The stunning architecture and peaceful ambiance make it an exceptional place.

The community here is warm, welcoming, and inclusive, and the facilities are clean and well-maintained.

Whether you're a regular worshipper or just visiting, you'll find a sense of unity and belonging at this mosque.

Overall, it's a beautiful place to nourish your soul and deepen your spiritual practice.

featured_reviews.review_id: Nagina Masjid (meaning 'Jewel Mosque') is a mosque in Champaner, Gujarat state, western India. It was built during the time of Mahmud Begada, in the 15th century, as were several other masjids, such as the Kevada, Bawaman, Ek Minar, Jama, Khajuri, and Shahar Ki.[1] It has minarets, globe-like domes, and narrow stairs.[2] It is part of the Champaner-Pavagadh Archaeological Park, a UNESCO World Heritage Site.[3]

hdiiss-
logo pr ek jmaanaa aisaa aaegaa kii msaajid meN dunyaa kii baate hoNgiiN

msjid meN bhii ibaadt kre to aadaabe msjid kaa khyaal rkheN
khii aisaa n ho ki thodddhii bhot ibaadt kr ke phir
msjid hii meN dunyaa kii baate,hNsii mjaak vgairaah shuruu kr de
aur yu nekiyaa kmaane ke bjaae nekiyaa ghumaa de
hdiisse paak meN hai
msjid meN hNsnaa qbr meN aNdheraa laataa hai
(al jaamiius sgiir pej 322 hdiiss 5231)
msjid meN mubaah (yaanii jaaiz) baat krnaa mkruhe /  (thriimii) hai
aur nekiyoN ko khaa jaataa hai
(miaqaatul mfaatiih jild 2 pej 449)

featured_reviews.review_translated_text:
Adabe Mosque
Hadish-
A time will come when people will talk about the world in the mosque.
Don't sit with them because they have nothing to do with Allah.
(Shuabul Iman Volume 3 Page 87 Hadith 2962)
Even if you pray in a mosque, keep in mind the etiquette of the mosque.
Lest it happen that after praying a little and then
Start talking about the world, joking etc. in the mosque itself.
And instead of earning good deeds, you give away good deeds.
Hadisha is in Pakistan
Laughing in the mosque brings darkness to the grave
(Al-Jami'us Sagheer page 322 Hadith 5231)
It is Makruh to talk about Mubah (i.e. permissible) in the mosque. (Tahrimi) is
and eats up good deeds
(Miaqatul Mafatih Volume 2 Page 449)
